Restore the f32 reference weight path (thread-pool parallel).

Upstream @ 568ef79 made the runtime W8A8 Q8P-only and removed the f32-dense weight
machinery. The add-on keeps f32 as an optional full-precision quant, so this
re-adds an f32 arm to each weight dispatcher in nemotron_asr_kernels.c, the f32
pointer in nemo_weight_t (nemotron_asr_kernels.h), and the F32 bind in the model
loader (nemotron_asr_model.c). The dense matvec is memory-bandwidth bound, so the
f32 arms run on the existing thread pool (output-dim split, no shared writes;
inner product is SIMD via nemo_dot_f32) rather than via wider vectors. bf16 is
not restored.

